
Exercise 1-22. Write a program to ‘‘fold’’ long input lines into two or more shorter lines after the last non-blank character that occurs before the n-th column of input. Make sure your program does something intelligent with very long lines, and ifthere are no blanks or tabs before the specified column. 

Exercise 1-23. Write a program to remove all comments from a C program. Don’t forget to handle quoted strings and character constants properly. C comments don’t nest. 

